data.content:
The root cause is that .NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which aligns with OpenAPI 3.1 and has several breaking changes. Here are the three key issues and fixes:

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` removed — use `System.Text.Json.Nodes`

Types like `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. are gone. Use `JsonNode` instead.

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

Other type mappings: `OpenApiInteger(42)` → `JsonValue.Create(42)`, `OpenApiBoolean(true)` → `JsonValue.Create(true)`, `OpenApiObject`/`OpenApiArray` → `JsonObject`/`JsonArray`.

### 2. `Schema.Nullable` removed — use `JsonSchemaType` flags

OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema's type arrays instead of a separate `nullable` flag. `OpenApiSchema.Type` is now a `JsonSchemaType` flags enum.

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;   // clear the Null flag
```

To **set** nullable: `schema.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null;`
To **check** nullable: `schema.Type.HasFlag(JsonSchemaType.Null)`

### 3. `OpenApiReference` / `ReferenceType` — constructor change

`OpenApiReference` moved to a constructor-based API:

```csharp
// Before
Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }

// After
Reference = new OpenApiReference("oauth2", ReferenceType.SecurityScheme)
```

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;          // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference("oauth2", ReferenceType.SecurityScheme)
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of changes:**
| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `new OpenApiReference { Type = ..., Id = ... }` | `new OpenApiReference("id", type)` |
